# KT Project Document

## Introduction

This document provides a comprehensive Knowledge Transfer (KT) for a sample web-based project. The purpose of this KT is to ensure smooth understanding and handover of the project to new team members.

## Project Overview

The project is a full-stack web application designed to manage user tasks and events. It includes a frontend built using HTML, CSS, JavaScript, and React, and a backend using Node.js and databases.

## Architecture

The system follows a client-server architecture. The frontend communicates with backend APIs, which handle business logic and database interactions.

## Frontend Details

The frontend is built using modern UI practices with responsive design, reusable components, and state management for better user experience.

## Backend Details

The backend is implemented using REST APIs. It handles authentication, data storage, and processing logic.

## Database Design

The database stores user data, tasks, and events. It includes tables for users, tasks, and logs.

## Authentication Flow

The system uses secure authentication with login and registration features, ensuring user data protection.

## Deployment

The application is deployed using cloud services with proper CI/CD pipelines for smooth updates.

## Error Handling

The project includes structured error handling to manage failures and improve debugging.

## Maintenance

Regular maintenance includes updating dependencies, monitoring logs, and optimizing performance.

## Conclusion

This KT ensures that the new developer can understand, maintain, and enhance the project effectively.
